<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-03-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-03-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="974" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d974">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.11/7433</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of the Navy</gloss>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Navy Department</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-03-14">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 14, 1916</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: In view of possible events requiring that
                            official aid should be afforded to American citizens resident in Mexico
                            to quit that country, and of the possible resulting duty that may
                            devolve upon the Navy Department in meeting such a necessity, I have the
                            honor to request that I be furnished promptly with as complete data as
                            may be practicable, giving the names of the ports, both on the east and
                            west coasts of Mexico, at which American refugees may be collected, and,
                            as nearly as can be foretold, the numbers that are likely to need aid in
                            leaving each port.</p>
                        <p>Sincerely yours,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Josephus Daniels</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>